A girl I was friends with in elementary school committed suicide after the first day of school. I was starting my freshman year and she was starting her junior year. She was in choir and band and was super talented. She always seemed so happy, so it was a big shock for everyone. Our principal came in to every class on the second day of school to break the news.
Then in my sophomore or junior year, a kid who'd been fighting brain cancer since elementary school died. I'd known him for a good 10 years. He really fought though and was a huge inspiration to so many people. His name was Kevin Cordasco.
